Class WolfScheduler

      • addCourse

        public boolean addCourse(java.lang.String name,
                         java.lang.String section)
        Checks if a given course (identified by name and section) can be added to the schedule and then adds it if allowed
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the course
        section - the section for the course
        Returns:
        true if it can be added (i.e. it is not already in the schedule), false if it does not exist in the course catalog
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the course is already in the schedule

      • addEvent

        public void addEvent(java.lang.String title,
                     java.lang.String meetingDays,
                     int startTime,
                     int endTime,
                     int weeklyRepeat,
                     java.lang.String eventDetails)
        Adds a user-defined event to the schedule if an event with the same title does not already exist
        Parameters:
        title - The title of the event
        meetingDays - The days the event takes place
        startTime - The start time of the event
        endTime - The end time of the event
        weeklyRepeat - The number of weeks the event repeats for
        eventDetails - Details describing the event
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the user attempts to add an event with the same title as another event already in the schedule

      • removeActivity

        public boolean removeActivity(int idx)
        Checks if an activity at a given index can be removed from the student's schedule and then removes it if allowed
        Parameters:
        idx - The index of the activity to be removed from the schedule
        Returns:
        true if the course can be removed (i.e. it is in the schedule), false if it cannot be removed (it is not in the schedule)
